Discussion

The analysis successfully identified transcriptionally distinct pancreatic cell populations. Clustering results aligned with known biological cell types, demonstrating the effectiveness of single-cell RNA-seq analysis for identifying cellular heterogeneity.

The presence of highly variable genes suggests important transcriptional differences between pancreatic cell populations.

Conclusion

This project demonstrates a complete workflow for analyzing single-cell RNA sequencing data. Using Seurat, we identified pancreatic cell populations and explored gene expression variability across thousands of cells. The results highlight the power of single-cell transcriptomics for understanding cellular diversity and biological function.
